        "text": "<p>EVERYDAY CARE<br/>Remove jewelry before physical activities or exposure to water, chemicals, and direct sunlight. Some gemstones are more delicate and can be affected by heat, light, or contact with perfumes and cosmetics.<br/><br/>CLEANING AT HOME<br/>Use lukewarm water, mild soap, and a soft brush for most stones. Avoid ultrasonic cleaners and steam, as they may damage treated, porous, or inclusion-rich gemstones; always dry carefully with a soft cloth.<br/><br/>STORAGE<br/>Keep each piece separate to prevent scratches, especially between harder and softer stones. Store in soft pouches, away from heat, light, and extreme humidity, avoiding sudden temperature changes.</p>",
